[SN]TITLE[SN]
General Election 2015: Take part in BBC Radio Kent debates

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
BBC Radio Kent will be holding a series of radio debates with some of the county's candidates in the weeks leading up to the General Election.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The events will be hosted by presenters Julia George and Ian Collins and recorded for broadcast.
The first debate will be held at Acacia Hall in Dartford, at 19:30 BST on Monday 30 March.
Admission is free but by ticket only.
If you would like to be in the audience at the debate in Dartford, Medway or Thanet you can request tickets by emailing: Election2015@bbc.co.uk
